MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS/GG-12 level in the Federal Service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector performing duties such as:
1) Collecting, analyzing, interpreting, evaluating and integrating complex data from multiple sources in assessing the relevance and significance of developments;
2) Planning, implementing and maintaining databases for intelligence assignments required to process all-source material and the production of technical or operational intelligence;
3) Monitoring associated security requirements to safeguard sensitive information and sources;
4) Reviewing, assessing and recommending appropriate dissemination for substantive special intelligence detailing scientific, technical, strategic and general military intelligence reporting. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management website: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series
